  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). A broad UQ campaign covering inlet flow rate, rotational speed, and blood viscosity was conducted and documented in the validation report; parametric sweeps confirmed that hemolysis index predictions remain within acceptable bounds across the operating envelope.",
