      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Bench-level hemolysis validation against FDA pump experimental data",
      "description": "CFD predictions of normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against in-vitro measurements from the FDA generic centrifugal pump benchmark at five flow-speed operating points. RH < 1 criterion satisfied at all points. The validation report additionally documents a parametric UQ campaign in which inlet flow rate (±15%), rotational speed (±200 RPM), and dynamic blood viscosity (±0.5 mPa·s) were varied; Monte Carlo ensemble results confirmed that hemolysis index predictions remain within ±8% of the nominal value across the full uncertainty space, supporting model adequacy for the CPB COU.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Relative hemolysis index RH < 1.0 at all five operating points; NIH prediction within 20% of experimental mean.",
      "outcomeStatus": "passed"
    },
